stories.title: Gayle-force win
stories.summary:
At last, a win for the West Indies, dramatically snatched with three
wickets in the last over when another defeat seemed certain

stories.title: 9th Match, England v West Indies, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1618th ODI in cricket history

stories.title: Stewart confident for Saturday
stories.summary:
England's last over defeat at the hands of West Indies in the NatWest Series
match at Trent Bridge was disappointing but has not affected confidence levels ahead of the final against Zimbabwe at Lord's on Saturday, says Alec Stewart

stories.title: England warm up for final with thrilling contest
stories.summary:
England warmed up for Saturday's NatWest Series final against Zimbabwe by
narrowly losing a thrilling contest to the West Indies by just 3 runs - Alec
Stewart remaining not out on exactly 100

stories.title: Breathtaking finish - Stewart's gallant innings is not enough
stories.summary:
Alec Stewart's gallant century was not enough to stop West Indies winning by
three runs in a breathtaking finish to the last qualifying match before the
final of the NatWest Series

stories.title: West Indies go out with honour, Stewart stranded
stories.summary:
West Indies, eliminated from the final, nevertheless finished with honour by
recording a thrilling three-run victory over England at Trent Bridge

stories.title: West Indies fight-back
stories.summary:
A superb West Indian fightback has brought to life this final group match of
the NatWest Series at Trent Bridge in Nottingham

stories.title: England pleased with progress
stories.summary:
After 30 overs of the West Indian innings at Trent Bridge in the last of the
group matches in the NatWest Series, England could be well pleased with
their progress

stories.title: Sunny sky, good pitch and West Indies batting
stories.summary:
For once, sunny skies greeted the cricketers as England took on West Indies
in the final group match of the NatWest Series
